HEADWORD: Expurgation
<hw>Ex`pur*ga"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>expurgatio</ets> justification, excuse: cf. F.
<ets>expurgation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of expurgating, purging, or
cleansing; purification from anything noxious, offensive, sinful, or
erroneous.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

